			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<u>Job Opportunity:</u></p>
<p>
We are recruiting for a talented Sys Admin / DevOps Engineer passionate about scalable multitenant SaaS applications and operating large-scale distributed Linux systems. The company is a fast-growing SaaS company looking for a talented ops engineer to work closely with our growing development team to help maintain uptime as company continues to acquire new customers and scale systems.<br />
<br />
You will be responsible for the overall health and performance of the company&rsquo;s platform, and work will include tool development and contribution to the overall design of new platform features. You should have proven capabilities and deep Linux expertise and you will take primary responsibility for scaling the fast-growing analytics platform (built in Linux/Grails), while also improving security and redundancy.<br />
<br />
The ideal candidate is someone passionate about problem solving with a proven record of learning and implementing new technologies.<br />
<br />
<u>Responsibilities:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Ensure our systems are up and running well (99% uptime)</li>
<li>
Explore ways to improve our infrastructure</li>
<li>
Promote a culture of designing/building with testing and monitoring in mind</li>
<li>
Learn and implement new technologies or build them yourself in order to help us achieve unparalleled reliability</li>
<li>
Identify potential scaling issues in our infrastructure and help define how to monitor and fix them</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<u>Requirements:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Deep expertise with Linux</li>
<li>
Experience deploying and maintaining cloud-based systems (e.g., Rackspace, Amazon EC2)</li>
<li>
Experience with CDN&#39;s</li>
<li>
Experience with infrastructure monitoring software (e.g., Nagios)</li>
<li>
Experience working closely with a development team</li>
<li>
Operations experience</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<u>Bonus:</u></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience setting up and maintaining Hadoop clusters</li>
<li>
Experience with build systems like Ant, Maven, Gradle</li>
<li>
Experience with Puppet or Chef</li>
<li>
Experience with at least one scripting language (Perl, Python, Ruby, Groovy, etc.)</li>
<li>
Experience with database administration (Postgres and/or MySQL)</li>
<li>
Experience with Git/GitHub</li>
<li>
Understanding of networking principles like load balancing and proxying</li>
<li>
Background in security</li>
<li>
Experience with continuous integration tools like Jenkins, Hudson, or Teamcity</li>
<li>
Experience with log management</li>
</ul>
